close_reason: "pm plan command family implemented + registered, dispatched via runPlan; lifecycle (create/show/add-step/update-step/complete-step/block-step/reorder-step/remove-step/link/unlink/decision/discovery/validation/resume/approve/materialize) tested end-to-end; history hash chain verified after lifecycle in sandbox dogfood and dogfood-package-first.mjs."
body: "Implement the dedicated agent-optimized command family for Plan item lifecycle and step mutations.\n\nScope:\n- Add `pm plan create|show|add-step|update-step|complete-step|block-step|reorder-step|link|approve|materialize|close`.\n- All commands must mutate normal Plan items through pm store/history APIs only.\n- Every step mutation must append a history entry and preserve deterministic before/after patches.\n- Default read output should be brief TOON for agents; JSON must expose stable machine-gating fields.\n\nHarness behavior to mirror:\n- Codex: durable living plan with progress, decision log, validation, and restartable context.\n- Claude Code: plan before editing, no implementation until approval, task-level create/update/readback semantics.\n- Cursor: codebase research, clarifying questions, editable plan steps, file paths/code references, saveable future context.\n\nCommand contract details:\n- `pm plan create --title ... --scope ... --parent pm-xxxx --related pm-yyyy --from-search \"query\"` creates a Plan item and records search/duplicate-check evidence.\n- `pm plan show <ID> --depth brief|standard|deep --fields ... --json` supports progressive disclosure.\n- `pm plan add-step <ID> --title ... --body ... --depends-on pm-xxxx --related pm-yyyy --file path=... --test command=... --doc path=...` appends a stable step id.\n- `pm plan update-step <ID> <STEP> --status ... --evidence ... --owner ...` patches one step.\n- `pm plan link <ID> --step <STEP> --related pm-xxxx --kind related|blocks|blocked_by|depends_on|discovered_from|implements|verifies` adds step-level context.\n- `pm plan approve <ID>` marks the plan approved for execution but does not automatically edit files.\n- `pm plan materialize <ID> --steps ... --type Task --parent ...` creates implementation items from plan steps and links them back.\n\nInvariants:\n- Exactly one `in_progress` step by default; `--allow-multiple-active` is explicit for parallel agent plans.\n- Blocked steps require linked blocked-by item or blocked reason.\n- Superseded steps require rationale and optional replacement step/item id.\n- Plan close requires implemented/materialized, superseded, canceled, or analysis-only evidence.\n\nAcceptance:\n- Agents can use one command family instead of raw metadata surgery for plan steps.\n- Commands are deterministic, script-friendly, and covered in SDK contracts.\n- Error messages give retry guidance for missing step ids, invalid status transitions, unsafe materialization, and non-Plan item ids.\n- Focused unit/integration tests cover command parsing, mutations, history entries, projections, and materialization."
